<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Goldman cloud</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Much of the business of an investment =
bank=E2=80=99s sales and trading division consists of calling up clients an=
d saying =E2=80=9Chey you should do this trade, this trade would be good fo=
r you.=E2=80=9D Perhaps the trade would be good for the client. But the act=
ual point is that it would be good for the bank; the bank would collect som=
e commission or fee or spread or edge for executing or financing the trade.=
 If clients do lots of trades the bank makes lots of money. If clients do n=
ot do trades the bank makes no money.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This =
is obviously complicated and subtle and exhausting work. You have to call l=
ots of clients and suggest lots of trades, and if the suggestions are stupi=
d the clients won=E2=80=99t do the trades and will stop taking your calls a=
nd do trades with some other bank. So you have to think of trades that the =
client will like, which requires knowing a lot about the market and the cli=
ents.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ideally you will do such a good job o=
f (1) recommending good trades, (2) sounding smart while you do it and (3) =
taking the client to sporting events that the client will start calling=C2=
=A0<em>you=C2=A0</em>for trade ideas. Instead of you calling and saying =E2=
=80=9Chey you should do this trade,=E2=80=9D the client will call you and s=
ay =E2=80=9Chey what trades should I do?=E2=80=9D You have become a trusted=
 adviser whom the client relies on for ideas, which also means that the cli=
ent will execute those ideas with you and you=E2=80=99ll make a lot of mone=
y.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Can this all be automated? <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25892760.281658/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMS8xMS8zMC9nb2xkbWFuLXNhY2hzLXVudmVpbHMtYW1hem9uLWJhY2tlZC=
1jbG91ZC1zZXJ2aWNlLWZvci13YWxsLXN0cmVldC10cmFkaW5nLWZpcm1zLmh0bWw/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB5743f17d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Sure why not</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Goldman Sachs is getting into the cloud computing busi=
ness.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The bank is opening up access to its =
trove of market data and software tools to hedge funds and asset managers i=
n an offering designed with Amazon=E2=80=99s cloud division, CNBC has learn=
ed exclusively.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The move, the result of a t=
wo-year collaboration with AWS, puts 152-year-old Goldman in the unusual po=
sition of being a provider of cloud services for Wall Street, according to =
executives at the two firms. It=E2=80=99s part of Goldman CEO David Solomon=
=E2=80=99s push to use technology to better serve clients of the firm=E2=80=
=99s markets division, a trading juggernaut that has helped drive the firm=
=E2=80=99s results this year. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A h=
edge fund client who wanted to chart the correlation between a stock and cu=
rrency exchange rates, for instance, could take months to assemble and clea=
n the data and perform calculations with it, said [Goldman co-chief informa=
tion officer Marco] Argenti. Instead, by building applications atop data fe=
eds and analytic tools that Goldman itself uses, the analysis can be done i=
n minutes, he said.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIf this existe=
d we would=E2=80=99ve used it, but we had to build it for ourselves because=
 there really is nothing like this in the market,=E2=80=9D Argenti said. =
=E2=80=9CAll you need to do is assemble the interface and integrate it with=
 your application and then everything else is kind of taken care of for you=
.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The executives decline=
d to give details about how Goldman and AWS would share revenue from the jo=
int project, but Solomon told CNBC that he saw it as a way to further entre=
nch the firm with trading clients. Goldman plans to monetize the service th=
rough the trading and financing opportunities that it will generate, he sai=
d.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThis is something that enhances=
 the experience of our institutional clients and gives them access to our d=
ata and information,=E2=80=9D Solomon said. =E2=80=9CThe way we get paid fo=
r that is we get more of their wallet share because the overall experience =
and services we provide gives us more mindshare, more opportunities to trad=
e with them, to finance them and do things like that.=E2=80=9D</p></blockqu=
ote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a bank, you don=E2=80=99t want =
your hedge fund clients to spend months assembling and cleaning data and pe=
rforming calculations with it before doing a trade!=C2=A0You want them to d=
o trades=C2=A0<em>today</em>, not months from now. Honestly you=E2=80=99d b=
e fine if they did trades without analysis and calculations, but in modern =
financial markets that=E2=80=99s a hard pitch; =E2=80=9Clet us help you do =
the analysis quickly=E2=80=9D is the best you are going to do. What you wan=
t is for your clients to come to work every morning and think about trade i=
deas using a tool with your brand name on it, and also for them not to thin=
k about those ideas for too long before they call you to do the trade.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/25892760.281658/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDgtMDMvbm93LWFuLWFwcC1jYW4tcGl0Y2gtbWVyZ2Vycz9jbXBpZD1CQ=
kQxMjAxMjFfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRl=
ciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMTEyMDEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB530f3c65" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;"> talked last year</a> about another delightful Gold=
man tech project,[1] an app that it offered to investment banking clients =
=E2=80=9Cto identify sale or=C2=A0spin-off=C2=A0opportunities and possible =
takeover targets in the form of unloved or poorly performing company divisi=
ons.=E2=80=9D That is a really good trade-idea generator to leave with the =
client: If the client fiddles around with your app and it tells her =E2=80=
=9Cyou should divest a $10 billion business=E2=80=9D and she believes it, s=
he will almost certainly call you to do the divestiture and you=E2=80=99ll =
collect an eight-digit fee for it.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=
=9CHey here=E2=80=99s some market data=E2=80=9D is maybe less obviously luc=
rative, but on the other hand it=E2=80=99s much more general-purpose. You d=
on=E2=80=99t have to tell the client what trade to do. You just leave them =
with a machine that will help them generate trades and give them a general =
warm feeling about you.=C2=A0</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-conte=
